Body & Soul has released the full stage times for the 2022 edition of the festival, which takes place this weekend at Ballinlough Castle, in Co Westmeath. Highlights include a live performance from Róisín Murphy, who makes her Body & Soul debut, a DJ and AV set by Jon Hopkins, and a Sunday-night finale from Mogwai, alongside appearances by the Sampa the Great, Lisa O’Neill & Crash Ensemble, EFÉ, Sprints, Pillow Queens and Soda Blonde, as well as CMAT, King Kong Company, Lee Fields, Mother DJs, Yard Act and Yves Tumor. Below we bring you exclusive details of every act due to perform between Friday, June 17th, and Sunday, June 19th. (If you’re reading this on your phone, turn it sideways, for a better view.)